mention.text: Folkestone , England We have been fighting the bastards since 1066

the taxi driver 's response to my faint-hearted suggestion that the Channel tunnel , one end of which we were making our way toward , signaled a new epoch in Anglo-French relations Had the taxi driver 's read my mind , or just the same edition of the Sun , which that morning had offered the Black Death , Paris streets ankle deep in dog mess , and a comparatively high suicide rate -LRB- in France suicide relieves the daily grind -RRB- among my mind 10 reasons to hate the French
